      Extravaganza 2015 Lineup Predictions
      May 1, 2015 by Miranda Velasquez

      With Extravaganza right around the corner, there has been much speculation as to which artists are going to make the lineup. We were curious to know what other students thought, so a poll was conducted in order to measure who will most likely perform, and which artists students want to perform. The responses of 71 people were recorded. What do you think?

      Question: Who do you think will be at extravaganza?

      1).  I don’t know

      2). Flume

      via smh.com.au

      3). Fetty Wap

      via billboard.com

      4). Some EDM D.J.

      via nytehype.com

      5). Pharrell

      via inquisitr.com

      6). Ludacris

      via bet.com

      7.) Hozier

      via nymag.com

       

      Honorable Mentions: Madeon, Kid Cudi, J. Cole, Midnight City, Fire Department, Dom Kennedy, Lana del Rey, Group Love, Yeah Yeah Yeahs, My Chemical Romance, Odesza, Jack Johnson, Wu-Tang, Childish Gambino, Chris Brown, Jason Derulo etc.

      Question: Who do you want to see at Extravaganza?

      1). System of a Down

      via genius.com

      2). The Weeknd

      via nois3.com

      3). Kanye West

      4). Drake

      via knowyourmeme.com

      5). Beyoncé

      via consequenceofsound.net

      6). Arctic Monkeys

      via articmonkeysnews.com

      7). Big Sean

      via mtv.com

      Honorable Mentions: Rae Sremmurd, Royal Blood, Hardwell, Major Lazer, Flume, Nicki Minaj, Calvin Harris, Basecamp, Kid Cudi, Walk the Moon, Lykke Li, 2 Chainz, A$AP Ferg, Red Hot Chili Peppers, YG, Luke Bryan, Snoop Dogg, Bruno Mars, Rick Ross, Wiz Khalifa, Kygo, Skrillex, Ashanti, Kaskade, Green Day, Azealia Banks, The Veronicas, Bastille, and last but not least, Jesus.
